   VACCINE-TERROR (Undated) _ Last May, President Clinton unveiled
an ambitious plan to counter germ attacks by stockpiling vaccines
at strategic sites around the country so communities could fight
epidemics. While such major initiatives usually result from many
months and sometimes years of fierce debate, this one, federal and
private experts said in interviews, was developed in record time.
But today the multi-million-dollar plan is in jeopardy, the fragile
consensus having collapsed. By William J. Broad and Judith Miller.
(With graphic and photos.)
</P>
