A2658 &Cx1f; tad-z
r k &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-COMMENTARY-BJT08-COX     08-07 0459
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-COMMENTARY-BJT08-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    COX NEWS SERVICE WEEKEND COMMENTARY BUDGET
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   These columns for release the weekend of Saturday, August 8,
1998, are moving today to clients of the New York Times News
Service.
</P>
<P>
   All columns have moved, in the commentary (k) category. If you
have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the Cox News
Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   GLASS-COLUMN _ In theory, the Internet can offer users more
convenient and flexible ways of exchanging data or buying and
selling goods than traditional forms of trade or communication. But
broadly felt distrust hampers electronic commerce from reaching its
full potential. (Glass, Cox News Service) MOVED 8/6.
</P>
<P>
   TEEPEN-COLUMN _ I wish Clinton would call up Kenneth Starr and
say: You've been saying the president is just like any other Joe.
He gets no legal slack. Well, if I'm just Joe Citizen with a swank
address, I've been thinking and I've decided not to testify to your
grand jury after all. (Teepen, Cox News Service) MOVED 8/6.
</P>
<P>
   KLEINBERG-COLUMN _ Why did it not surprise me late last month to
read that files documenting gold stolen from Jews by the Nazis
mysteriously disappeared from German archives well after the
conclusion of World War II _ and that U.S. negligence played a
role? (Kleinberg, Cox News Service) MOVED 8/6.
</P>
<P>
   MURRAY-COLUMN _ A series of stories on my trip to the Baltics
will be forthcoming over the next couple of weeks. Meantime, there
are just two things I've learned from my travels. The second is how
to pack. (Murray, Cox News Service) MOVED 8/6.
</P>
<P>
   MCCARTY-COLUMN _ The more stressed out you are, the more you
need the outlet, the harder it is to find the time. But just you
wait. One of these days, we'll break free. We wanna spend too much,
we wanna stay too late, we wanna roar too loud, we wanna go too
far. At least for that one hour in aerobics class. (McCarty, Dayton
Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   WALKER-COLUMN _ During the first few years of my education,
unless it was raining, I hoofed it about six blocks to Marlin
Elementary. School starts for two of my children this week, and I
regret that they and their older sister have not had that same
experience and the camaraderie that went with it. (Walker, Longview
News Journal) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   CSIBLEY-COLUMN _ My mother's lifelong friend and neighbor, Sally
Barnes, was killed in an automobile accident in front of her
Alford, Fla., home this week. For my family, it was more than
losing a good friend, the mother of my children's best Alford
playmates. It was the end of a way of life. (Sibley, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED 8/7.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
