Grammy Award for best rock gospel album. Yet few people know about
the group's public campaign to promote racial unity. This
interracial trio created the ERACE (Eliminating Racism and Creating
Equality) Foundation last year to promote what they call ``living
integration.'' I talk to DC Talk member Toby McKeehan about their
campaign. (Blake, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
