<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    CUBA'S CASTRO TAKING THE DIPLOMATIC ROUTE
 &HT;    With CUBA-CASTRO-$ADV09.
 &HT;    For Use Saturday, Aug. 8 And Thereafter.
 &HT;    By SHELLEY EMLING 
 &HT;    c.1998 Cox News Service 
<TEXT>
<P>
   FIDEL CASTRO: DIPLOMATIC BREAKTHROUGHS
</P>
<P>
   January: Pope John Paul II visits Cuba and criticizes U.S.
embargo.
</P>
<P>
   January: Guatemala restores diplomatic relations with Cuba.
</P>
<P>
   April: Canadian Prime Minister Jean Chretien visits Cuba and
announces increased bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
   April: A French business delegation announces millions of
dollars in new investments in Cuba.
</P>
<P>
   April: Spain names a new ambassador to Cuba ending a
long-standing diplomatic feud.
</P>
<P>
   April: The Dominican Republic restores diplomatic relations with
Cuba.
</P>
<P>
   July: Fidel Castro makes a six-day swing through the Caribbean,
visiting Jamaica, Barbados and Grenada.
</P>
<P>
   August: Fidel Castro scheduled to visit the Dominican Republic,
his first visit there since the 1959 Communist revolution.
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
