parents packed their kids off to the first day of school with a new
metal lunch box and an apple for the teacher. Nowadays, parents are
supposed to follow a week-by-week countdown (much like planning a
wedding) to get their children ready for school, according to an
article in Crayola Kids magazine. By Barbara De Witt. 
. 
