<P>
   BELLSOUTH-VENEZUELA _ One week after BellSouth Corp. (BLS)
failed to participate in the landmark privatization of Brazil's
national phone company, the Baby Bell revealed that it is
increasing its stake in Venezuela's largest wireless operator.
(Kanell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   BELLSOUTH-STRIKE _ Advance on the BellSouth negotiations that
face a deadline of 11:59 Saturday. Progress is being made, but
obstacles remain and in the balance are the jobs of about 48,000
workers and the daily work of the $22 billion-a-year company _ not
to mention the image of the good neighbor BellSouth has pumped
millions of dollars into cultivating. (Kanell, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   AGL-EARNINGS _AGL Resources, parent of Atlanta Gas Light Co.
reporting quarterly earnings in advance of deregulation of the
Georgia gas market this fall. Low consumption summer months don't
usually mean much to the company's financial picture. (Kanell,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   SHARP-DRIVING _ ATLANTA _ When it was first announced we would
be getting HOV lanes on the freeways in metro Atlanta, I was less
than impressed. I have since changed my opinion. When I have had
the opportunity, I have found them to be not only efficient, but
stress-reducing. (Sharp, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) l, f. MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TEST-DRIVE _ ATLANTA -- Less than 10 years after it was
introduced as a 1990 model, the midsize Chevrolet Lumina sedan is
one of the vehicles reportedly headed for the ax if General Motors
carries out the talked-about thinning of its product line. Here are
four reasons it's been tagged a ``blue light'' special, a ``best
buy'' and a car that ``does most things adequately, but
unexceptionally.'' (DeVault, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) l, f.
MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   MECHANIC _ ATLANTA -- For the past couple of weeks I have been
addressing the issue of fuel octane as it relates to engine
requirements. (Carter, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) l, f. MOVED.
</P>
