Lawrence Walsh and Marion Barry's prosecutors. Now, Judy Smith is
facing the media circus as spokesperson for Monica Lewinsky and her
mother. By Aaron Zitner. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   BROKEN-TRUST (Farmington, N.H.) _ When Thomas Harding discovered
that teenage son had been sexually abused by their parish priest,
he notified authorities. The priest has now been convicted and the
Hardings, devout Catholics, must deal with a shaken faith in their
church. By Brian MacQuarrie. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   CROWDED-CEMETERY (Bourne, Mass.) -- As the World War II
generation passes away in record numbers, the Massachusetts
National Cemetery in Bourne is struggling to keep up with funerals.
By Bruce Mohl. 1100 words.
</P>
