<P>
   JAPAN-OBUCHI (Tokyo) _ In his first major policy speech since
taking over as prime minister a week ago, Keizo Obuchi on Friday
proposed cuts in individual and corporate taxes, steps toward
deregulating the economy, cuts in government spending and new
public spending. By Stephanie Strom.
</P>
