<P>
   GM-STRIKE-IMPACT (Traverse City, Mich.) _ The nearly
eight-week-long strike this summer at two General Motors parts
factories will continue to hurt the automaker's sales until
October, and some customers have been permanently lost, GM's top
marketing executive said Friday. By Keith Bradsher.
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET.)
</P>
<P>
   MARKET (New York) _ The stock market rallied for a third day
Friday as investors bought stocks whose prices had been pummeled
during, and even before, the headline-grabbing selloff that began
in mid-July. But the major market measures still ended the week
down sharply, with the Dow Jones industrial average off 3.2 percent
and the Standard &AMP; Poor's index of 500 stocks down 2.8 percent. By
Jonathan Fuerbringer.
</P>
