<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer pnans to move the following
stories for clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of
Saturday, Aug. 8, and thereafter. If you have any questions, please
call Tina May at (206) 448-8355.
</P>
<P>
   BOEING-CONDIT (Seattle) What started out as just another rumor
that heads were about to roll at Boeing _ namely Chairman Phil
Condit's _ has taken on a life of its own, with some analysts
attributing the company's stock rise yesterday to the news. While
Boeing officials refused to dignify the rumors earlier in the week,
yesterday they categorically denied them. Boeing President Harry
Stonecipher even sent his own e-mail response to the ``Grape Vine
News'' that was sent directly to him. ``You better get yourself a
new grapevine because the one you have is seriously flawed and
useless,'' Stonecipher wrote. ``It is wrong on all counts.''
</P>
