<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-07 20:27 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A3899 &Cx1f; tad-z
u f &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-ATL-BELLSOUTH08-STRIK     08-07 0993
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-ATL-BELLSOUTH08-STRIKE </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    BellSouth, union report progress
 &HT;    By Michael E. Kanell
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA -- With the contract for most BellSouth employees set to
expire at 11:59 tonight negotiators for the union and company kept
talking, claiming progress toward a last-minute agreement.
</P>
<P>
   Bargainers aim to nail down deals on contracts for six units
that represent 48,000 union workers. The teams for BellSouth and
