<P>
   LA-MURDER-SUICIDE (Los Angeles) _ A man and his wife were found
dead Friday morning in their home in a suburban Los Angeles
neighborhood in an apparent murder-suicide. Neighbors and relatives
said David Schenk and Heather Fredette had a tumultuous
relationship that often drew authorities to the home. A week ago
Schenk held Fredette down, put a gun to her head and threatened to
kill her. The ordeal, which authorities described as terrifying,
prompted Fredette to obtain a restraining order. But, despite the
report she made of the gun terrorism, sheriff's deputies failed to
arrest Schenk. By Jesse Hiestand. (Will run in the ``n'' California
news file.)
</P>
<P>
   LA-KID-SHOOTER (Los Angeles) _ Police renewed warnings to lock
guns away from children after Victor Alvarez died of a gunshot
wound to the head. Alvarez was shot three weeks ago when a boy, 4,
wandered into the converted garage where Alvarez and four other men
lived. The boy picked a shotgun up from the floor, it discharged
and Alvarez was hit. He died Thursday at Pacifica Hospital. By
Deborah Sullivan. (Will move in the ``n'' California news file.)
</P>
<P>
   PORN-PROTEST (Los Angeles) _ It's touted as a forum on First
Amendment freedoms, so why is Larry Flynt's daughter going to
picket the Center for Sex Research's World Pornography Conference
at L.A.'s California State University, Northridge? Residents
complained that the center was improperly legitimizing questionable
behavior. By Melissa Schmitt. (Will move in the ``n'' California
news file.)
</P>
<P>
   FHS-CEO (Los Angeles) _ Foundation Health Systems Inc., the
fourth-largest publicly traded U.S. managed-care company, named its
chief operating officer, Jay Gellert, as its new chief executive,
replacing Malik Hasan. By Greg Wilcox.
</P>
<P>
   (Will move in the ``f'' financial news wire.)
</P>
<P>
