announced late Friday it is suing the NCAA for $267 million because
the collegiate organization wants to ban aluminum bats. Easton is
one of the largest makers of the metal bats. By Patrick Hipes.
(Will move in the ``f'' financial and ``s'' sports news wire.)
</P>
