talking recently at a campaign kickoff in Chicago for the plan to
join with the Council of Jewish Federations. Jews are sharply
divided these days over questions such as who can call themselves
Jewish. So splits have developed in how big donors want their money
to be spent. (Steve Kagan/New York Times Photo)
</P>
