Conga Room conjures up the heat of the Caribbean and Latin America.
(Jill Connelly/New York Times Photo) *LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT3) LOS ANGELES -- Aug. 7, 1998 -- ADV. FOR SUN., AUG. 9 --
CONGA-ROOM-1, 8-7 -- Touch dancing is the rule, and at the Conga
Room, younger dancers mix with seasoned veterans. Sex roles are
very much in force. Men ask women to dance, and they'd better know
how to lead. Unlike the look-but-don't-touch vibe of some other
clubs, the Conga Room conjures up the heat of the Caribbean and
Latin America. (Marissa Roth/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT2) UNDATED -- Aug. 7, 1998 -- ADV. FOR SUN., AUG. 9 --
ABOUT-CARS-NISSAN-QUEST, 8-7 -- The redesigned 1999 Nissan Quest
mini-van keeps its old body structure and retains its relatively
agile handling, but it gains another door and adds horsepower and
cargo capacity. For 1999, the Quest's wheelbase is unchanged at
112.2 inches, but the body has been stretched nearly 5 inches and
it is about an inch wider. (New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT1) EAST LEMPSTER, N.H. -- Aug. 7, 1998 --
MOTOCROSS-FAMILY-BOS, 8-7 -- At the Jolly Roger Moto-Sports Park,
Mark Robinson, center, gives his son Jacob, 5, some words of
encouragement before the start of his first motorcross race. Jacob,
who underwent surgery for Arnold-Chiari Syndrome, a rare brain
malformation in which part of the cerebellum pushes down against
the spinal canal, now joins his two brothers in in motocross
competition. (Michael Robinson-Chavez/Boston Globe Photo)
</P>
